description: Erection of a 27-storey tower (110m) plus basement and roof enclosure and part 1, part 4 to 10-storey buildings plus basement and roof enclosures providing for: 720 residential dwellings (class C3); 10,820sqm of business floorspace (class B1); 2,389sqm of shop floorspace (class A1); 1,112sqm of restaurant/caf floorspace (class A3); 907sqm of flexible shop/restaurant/caf floorspace (class A1/A3); student accommodation  160 rooms (class sui-generis) and a hotel  125 rooms (class C1) including the creation of landscaped public open space and private/semi-private amenity spaces, pedestrian routes, 1035 cycle spaces, 35 motorcycle spaces, 50 car-parking spaces, electrical sub-stations and other associated works.
decision_conditions:
CONDITION:  The development hereby permitted shall be begun not later than the expiration of five years from the date of this permission.

REASON:  To comply with the provisions of Section 91(1)(a) of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 as amended by the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004 (Chapter 5); and as a five year planning consent is appropriate given the special circumstances, size and complexity of the development.
